<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏃 RB001 Week 1 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Your First Script · <strong>Course:</strong> Obby Architect · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week you wrote your first script in Roblox Studio. <code>print</code> sends a message to the <strong>Output</strong> window, and <code>script.Parent</code> is the part your script lives inside.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the script. Before you run anything, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">print(&quot;Hello&quot;)
print(&quot;Obby&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Does the Output window show <code>Hello</code> first? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">script.Parent.Color = Color3.fromRGB(255, 0, 0)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>This script is inside a platform. Does the platform turn red? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows clean code first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The script should print <code>Hello!</code> in the Output window.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
print(&quot;Hello!&quot;)
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
print(Hello!)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The script should turn the platform blue. Look at the property name very carefully.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
script.Parent.Color = Color3.fromRGB(0, 0, 255)
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
script.Parent.Colour = Color3.fromRGB(0, 0, 255)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The script should change the color of the part it lives inside. One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">script.____.Color = Color3.fromRGB(255, 0, 0)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>Parent</code> · <code>print</code> · <code>Color3</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p>The script should send a message to the Output window. One word is missing.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">____(&quot;My obby is open!&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>print</code> · <code>Parent</code> · <code>script</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your own obby in Roblox Studio. Use a script to recolor your obby platforms by code. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your recolored obby, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I changed the color with …</p>
<p>My favorite color was … because …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you show your Roblox Studio screen. Talk like you are teaching a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>script</strong>, <strong>Output</strong>, <strong>print</strong>, <strong>Color3</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Run the game and show your <code>print</code> message in the Output window.</li>
<li>Point at a platform your code recolored.</li>
<li>Say in your own words what <code>print</code> does.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
